RESOURCE.INFO: -- output format : csv SELECT TOP 100 "II/328/allwise".AllWISE, "II/328/allwise".RAJ2000, "II/328/allwise".DEJ2000, "II/328/allwise".W1mag, "II/328/allwise".e_W1mag, "II/328/allwise".W2mag, "II/328/allwise".e_W2mag, "II/328/allwise".W3mag, "II/328/allwise".e_W3mag, "II/328/allwise".W4mag, "II/328/allwise".e_W4mag, "II/328/allwise".Jmag, "II/328/allwise".e_Jmag, "II/328/allwise".Hmag, "II/328/allwise".e_Hmag, "II/328/allwise".Kmag, "II/328/allwise".e_Kmag, "II/328/allwise".ccf, "II/328/allwise".ex, "II/328/allwise".var, "II/328/allwise".pmRA, "II/328/allwise".e_pmRA, "II/328/allwise".pmDE, "II/328/allwise".e_pmDE, "II/328/allwise".qph, "II/328/allwise".d2M FROM "II/328/allwise"

FIELD.name: AllWISE
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: WISE All-Sky Release Catalog name, based on J2000 position (designation)

FIELD.name: W1mag
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ? W1 magnitude (3.35um) {\fg{red4}Red values} correspond to upper limits (S/N<2)

FIELD.name: W2mag
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ? W2 magnitude (4.6um) {\fg{red4}Red values} correspond to upper limits (S/N<2)

FIELD.name: W3mag
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ? W3 magnitude (11.6um) {\fg{red4}Red values} correspond to upper limits (S/N<2)

FIELD.name: W4mag
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ? W4 magnitude (22.1um) {\fg{red4}Red values} correspond to upper limits (S/N<2)

FIELD.name: Jmag
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ? 2MASS J magnitude (1.25um) {\fg{red4}Red values} correspond to upper limits (S/N<2)

FIELD.name: Hmag
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ? 2MASS H magnitude (1.65um) {\fg{red4}Red values} correspond to upper limits (S/N<2)

FIELD.name: Kmag
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ? 2MASS Ks magnitude (2.17um) {\fg{red4}Red values} correspond to upper limits (S/N<2)

FIELD.name: ccf
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: [0DHOPdhop] Contamination and confusion flag, one per band (cc_flags) (2)

FIELD.name: d2M
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: ? Distance separating the positions of the WISE source and associated 2MASS PSC source
